19/03/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Former Interior Minister Ivan Jarnjak was interviewed Thursday (18 March) by investigators of the International Criminal Tribunal for the former Yugoslavia. Afterwards, Jarnjak said the talks would continue on Friday. No official information was provided; however, investigators are reportedly interested in the 1992-1996 period when Jarnjak served as interior minister and chairman of the parliamentary committee on internal affairs and national security. (Croatian Radio, HINA - 18/03/04)
